criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  be 18 years of age;

          -  be hospitalized for performing surgical oncology;

          -  not be performing another treatment for cancer;

          -  not be participating in another study;

          -  be clinically well and / or stable (have score less than or equal to 3 by the Eastern
             Cooperative Oncology Group - Performance Status).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  being illiterate, a condition that will prevent the participant to answer the
             questionnaires and instruments of the study, which are self-administered;

          -  be in possession of psychiatric disorders;

          -  be using medication containing corticosteroids.
